The syntax for creating a new group identifier in SQL Actian 4GL is:
```sql
create group group_id {, group_id}
              [with users = (user_id {, user_id})];
```
Here's an example of using the create group statement to create a new group with a valid object name "tel\_sales":
```sql
create group tel_sales with users = (harryk, joanb);
```
In this example, the group identifier "tel\_sales" is created and associated with two users ("harryk" and "joanb"). Additional users can be added to the group using the `alter group` statement.
